x\longrightarrow (x-y)+y.
\frac{x}{x+y}\longrightarrow\frac{(x+y)-y}{x+y}=\frac{x+y}{x+y}-\frac{y}{x+y}=1-\frac{y}{x+y}.
\frac{x^2}{1+x^2} = \frac{(1 - 1) + x^2}{1+x^2} = \frac{1+x^2}{1+x^2}-\frac{1}{1+x^2} = 1 - \frac{1}{1+x^2}
